	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="/images/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have to agree, if you are fighting these or fire elementals, the way to go is cancel magic (sometimes you have to cancel twice), then burn and/or melee.  With the recent patch, cancel magic acts like a taunt, and will IMMEDIATELY aggro it on you.<BR>
  With my mage, I usually fireshield pet, cancel magic on imp, sic pet on him, burn a few times, then fireshield myself and melee till done.  I come out with 80 hp, 40 mana and pet is usually around 50.  Loot is not bad.  I take blues and evens, and will take a yellow with FM, and full HP, and a good pet.  If I don't melee myself (with FS), I'll usually lose my pet.<BR>
  And these things can pull nasty trains, so make sure it's a solo pull.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
